data.title: What's not to like
data.text: If you are in the mood for a subway sandwich this is it. Hot , fresh and stuffed.It gets very busy at noon. I try to go before or slightly after lunch, but if I can't they are still quick.

data.title: AWFUL SUBWAY & PHILLY CHEESE STEAK Restaurant Fl. .
data.text: he Subway at Walmart in Greenacres FL & The Philly Cheese Steak restaurant in Boynton Beach Fl. must be owned by the same Franchisee.  BOTH Forgot;    onions..used hamburger meat instead of B/angus beef. Cheese was like disgusting clotted milk, & almost non existent....Both seemed to be cutting corners everywhere indicating going out of business.  We shall never go again nor any of my pals....Friends don't let friends eat garbage...

data.title: Meat arrives in a Semi Truck its not fresh
data.text: Seen a smoking truck driver delivering their meat from a semi truck, it is not fresh at all. The serves is bad always young kids left alone to run the place and they have no manors and they don't care.

data.title: Love it
data.text: I love coming here because you can always get a deal but when I went I met the nicest worker and he built my sandwich well and I cannot wait to go back.
